Oval and strongly macropterous (
figure 6
). Head from above sub-rectangular to semi-lunar in outline, about 4.17x as broad as long; in front somewhat ovoid (
figure 7
), about 1.48x as broad as high. Vertex and frons dense with dark-red punctures, generally dark reddish-brown interspersed with some pale testaceous to ivory-white rugosities; latter coalescing to form three distinct transverse stripes towards apex of frons at the level of ventral eye margin, and a fourth on apical frontal margin. Post occipital margin contrasting ivory-white. Apical fontal margin convex, slightly indented medially, occluding only base of tylus and juga. Tylus strongly deflexed, depressed along middle so its base together with juga appear as three tubercle-like prominences at apex of head in frontal view (
figure 6
). Entire head disk strongly shining, glabrous. Gena low, 0.2x as high as eye. Eyes apparently dark-red (large patches bleached in specimen), glabrous; very weakly emarginated caudomesally behind ocelli. Latter large, colourless with surrounding annuli dark-red; rather strongly protuberant, 1.33x width of each apart.

Strongly ovate and macropterous (
figure 8
). Head strongly appressed, inclined forwards, about 1.79–2.27x as broad as long from above; in front quadrate (
figure 9
), about 1.31–1.38x as broad as high. Frons tumid convex apically, elongated ventrad, virtually occluding tylus and juga; apical margin weakly indented medially, outlined with somewhat interrupted ivory-white rugosity. Genae high, distinctly produced ventrad beyond frontal margin, about 0.44–0.47x as high as eyes. Entire head disk apparently glabrous, thickset with dark reddish-brown punctures interspersed with pale to ivory-white coalescing rugosities; these forming rather distinct transverse stripes at apex of frons as follows: two running from side to side immediately beneath eyes with the distal one connected to a third considerably shorter and less discrete one (
figure 9
). Eyes dark-red to blackish (extensively bleached in 
two specimens
), glabrous and not emarginate behind ocelli. Latter 3x width of each apart, dark-red to black with distinct concolourous surrounding annuli.
